Comment>
-   Consume a diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and whole grains.
-   Limit intake of saturated and trans fats, found in red meat, full-fat dairy products, and processed foods.
-   Choose lean sources of protein such as chicken, fish, beans, and legumes.
-   Eat foods high in soluble fiber, such as oats, barley, and beans.
Include foods rich in omega-3 fatty acids, such as fatty fish, flaxseeds, and walnuts.
-   Avoid or limit alcohol consumption.
